{{see|Ton}}
{{wikipedia}}
==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A unit of [[weight]] ([[mass]]) equal to 2240 [[pound]]s (a long ton) or 2000 pounds (a short ton) or 1000 [[kilogram]]s (a metric ton).
# A unit of [[volume]]; [[register ton]].
# A unit of [[power]] in refrigeration and air conditioning, equal to 12,000 Btu/h (3.517 kilowatts).
# (''colloquial''; ''also in plural'' '''tons''') A large amount.
#:''I’ve got a ton of work to do.''
# (''slang'') A speed of 100 [[mile per hour|miles per hour]].
# (''slang'') One hundred [[pound sterling|pounds sterling]].
# (''cricket'') One hundred runs.

====Synonyms====
*(''large amount''): [[heap]], [[load]], [[pile]]
*(''one-hundred runs''): [[century]]

